verses.text_plain: Blessed are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
1Blessed are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the Lord. ▼
▼ undefiled: or, perfect, or, sincere

footnotes.body_html: ▼ undefiled: or, perfect, or, sincere

verses.text_plain: Blessed are they that keep his testimonies, and that seek him with the whole heart.
verses.verse_html: 2Blessed are they that keep his testimonies, and that seek him with the whole heart.

verses.text_plain: They also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.
verses.verse_html: 3They also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast commanded us to keep thy precepts diligently.
verses.verse_html: 4Thou hast commanded us to keep thy precepts diligently.

verses.text_plain: O that my ways were directed to keep thy statutes!
verses.verse_html: 5O that my ways were directed to keep thy statutes!

verses.text_plain: Then shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 6Then shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all thy commandments.

tokens.text: Then shall I not be ashamed

verses.text_plain: I will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned thy righteous judgments.
verses.verse_html:
7I will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned thy righteous judgments. ▼
▼ thy…: Heb. judgments of thy righteousness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy…: Heb. judgments of thy righteousness
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy…: Heb. judgments of thy righteousness

verses.text_plain: I will keep thy statutes: O forsake me not utterly.
verses.verse_html: 8I will keep thy statutes: O forsake me not utterly.

verses.text_plain: Wherewithal shall a young man cleanse his way? by taking heed thereto according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 9Wherewithal shall a young man cleanse his way? by taking heed thereto according to thy word.

verses.text_plain: With my whole heart have I sought thee: O let me not wander from thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 10With my whole heart have I sought thee: O let me not wander from thy commandments.

tokens.text: thee: O let me not wander

verses.text_plain: Thy word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee.
verses.verse_html: 11Thy word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee.

verses.text_plain: Blessed art thou, O Lord: teach me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 12Blessed art thou, O Lord: teach me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: With my lips have I declared all the judgments of thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 13With my lips have I declared all the judgments of thy mouth.

verses.text_plain: I have rejoiced in the way of thy testimonies, as much as in all riches.
verses.verse_html: 14I have rejoiced in the way of thy testimonies, as much as in all riches.

verses.text_plain: I will meditate in thy precepts, and have respect unto thy ways.
verses.verse_html: 15I will meditate in thy precepts, and have respect unto thy ways.

verses.text_plain: I will delight myself in thy statutes: I will not forget thy word.
verses.verse_html: 16I will delight myself in thy statutes: I will not forget thy word.

verses.text_plain: Deal bountifully with thy servant, that I may live, and keep thy word.
verses.verse_html: 17Deal bountifully with thy servant, that I may live, and keep thy word.

verses.text_plain: Open thou mine eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of thy law.
verses.verse_html:
18Open thou mine eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of thy law. ▼
▼ Open: Heb. Reveal

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Open: Heb. Reveal

verses.text_plain: I am a stranger in the earth: hide not thy commandments from me.
verses.verse_html: 19I am a stranger in the earth: hide not thy commandments from me.

verses.text_plain: My soul breaketh for the longing that it hath unto thy judgments at all times.
verses.verse_html: 20My soul breaketh for the longing that it hath unto thy judgments at all times.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast rebuked the proud that are cursed, which do err from thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 21Thou hast rebuked the proud that are cursed, which do err from thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: Remove from me reproach and contempt; for I have kept thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html: 22Remove from me reproach and contempt; for I have kept thy testimonies.

verses.text_plain: Princes also did sit and speak against me: but thy servant did meditate in thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 23Princes also did sit and speak against me: but thy servant did meditate in thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Thy testimonies also are my delight and my counsellors.
verses.verse_html:
24Thy testimonies also are my delight and my counsellors. ▼
▼ my counsellors: Heb. men of my counsel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ my counsellors: Heb. men of my counsel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ my counsellors: Heb. men of my counsel

verses.text_plain: My soul cleaveth unto the dust: quicken thou me according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 25My soul cleaveth unto the dust: quicken thou me according to thy word.

tokens.text: thou me according to thy word

verses.text_plain: I have declared my ways, and thou heardest me: teach me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 26I have declared my ways, and thou heardest me: teach me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Make me to understand the way of thy precepts: so shall I talk of thy wondrous works.
verses.verse_html: 27Make me to understand the way of thy precepts: so shall I talk of thy wondrous works.

verses.text_plain: My soul melteth for heaviness: strengthen thou me according unto thy word.
verses.verse_html:
28My soul melteth for heaviness: strengthen thou me according unto thy word. ▼
▼ melteth: Heb. droppeth

tokens.text: thou me according unto thy word

footnotes.body_html: ▼ melteth: Heb. droppeth

verses.text_plain: Remove from me the way of lying: and grant me thy law graciously.
verses.verse_html: 29Remove from me the way of lying: and grant me thy law graciously.

verses.text_plain: I have chosen the way of truth: thy judgments have I laid before me.
verses.verse_html: 30I have chosen the way of truth: thy judgments have I laid before me.

verses.text_plain: I have stuck unto thy testimonies: O Lord, put me not to shame.
verses.verse_html: 31I have stuck unto thy testimonies: O Lord, put me not to shame.

verses.text_plain: I will run the way of thy commandments, when thou shalt enlarge my heart.
verses.verse_html: 32I will run the way of thy commandments, when thou shalt enlarge my heart.

verses.text_plain: Teach me, O Lord, the way of thy statutes; and I shall keep it unto the end.
verses.verse_html: 33Teach me, O Lord, the way of thy statutes; and I shall keep it unto the end.

verses.text_plain: Give me understanding, and I shall keep thy law; yea, I shall observe it with my whole heart.
verses.verse_html: 34Give me understanding, and I shall keep thy law; yea, I shall observe it with my whole heart.

verses.text_plain: Make me to go in the path of thy commandments; for therein do I delight.
verses.verse_html: 35Make me to go in the path of thy commandments; for therein do I delight.

verses.text_plain: Incline my heart unto thy testimonies, and not to covetousness.
verses.verse_html: 36Incline my heart unto thy testimonies, and not to covetousness.

verses.text_plain: Turn away mine eyes from beholding vanity; and quicken thou me in thy way.
verses.verse_html:
37Turn away mine eyes from beholding vanity; and quicken thou me in thy way. ▼
▼ Turn…: Heb. Make to pass

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Turn…: Heb. Make to pass

verses.text_plain: Stablish thy word unto thy servant, who is devoted to thy fear.
verses.verse_html: 38Stablish thy word unto thy servant, who is devoted to thy fear.

verses.text_plain: Turn away my reproach which I fear: for thy judgments are good.
verses.verse_html: 39Turn away my reproach which I fear: for thy judgments are good.

verses.text_plain: Behold, I have longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 40Behold, I have longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousness.

verses.text_plain: Let thy mercies come also unto me, O Lord, even thy salvation, according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 41Let thy mercies come also unto me, O Lord, even thy salvation, according to thy word.

verses.text_plain: So shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me: for I trust in thy word.
verses.verse_html:
42So shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me: for I trust in thy word. ▼
▼ So…: or, So shall I answer him that reproveth me in a thing

footnotes.body_text: ▼ So…: or, So shall I answer him that reproveth me in a thing
footnotes.body_html: ▼ So…: or, So shall I answer him that reproveth me in a thing

verses.text_plain: And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth; for I have hoped in thy judgments.
verses.verse_html: 43And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth; for I have hoped in thy judgments.

verses.text_plain: So shall I keep thy law continually for ever and ever.
verses.verse_html: 44So shall I keep thy law continually for ever and ever.

verses.text_plain: And I will walk at liberty: for I seek thy precepts.
verses.verse_html:
45And I will walk at liberty: for I seek thy precepts. ▼
▼ at liberty: Heb. at large

footnotes.body_html: ▼ at liberty: Heb. at large

verses.text_plain: I will speak of thy testimonies also before kings, and will not be ashamed.
verses.verse_html: 46I will speak of thy testimonies also before kings, and will not be ashamed.

verses.text_plain: And I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved.
verses.verse_html: 47And I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved.

verses.text_plain: My hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 48My hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Remember the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.
verses.verse_html: 49Remember the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.

tokens.text: upon which thou hast caused me to hope

verses.text_plain: This is my comfort in my affliction: for thy word hath quickened me.
verses.verse_html: 50This is my comfort in my affliction: for thy word hath quickened me.

verses.text_plain: The proud have had me greatly in derision: yet have I not declined from thy law.
verses.verse_html: 51The proud have had me greatly in derision: yet have I not declined from thy law.

verses.text_plain: I remembered thy judgments of old, O Lord; and have comforted myself.
verses.verse_html: 52I remembered thy judgments of old, O Lord; and have comforted myself.

verses.text_plain: Horror hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.
verses.verse_html: 53Horror hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.

tokens.text: upon me because of the wicked

verses.text_plain: Thy statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.
verses.verse_html: 54Thy statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.

verses.text_plain: I have remembered thy name, O Lord, in the night, and have kept thy law.
verses.verse_html: 55I have remembered thy name, O Lord, in the night, and have kept thy law.

verses.text_plain: This I had, because I kept thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 56This I had, because I kept thy precepts.

tokens.text: This I had, because I kept

verses.text_plain: Thou art my portion, O Lord: I have said that I would keep thy words.
verses.verse_html: 57Thou art my portion, O Lord: I have said that I would keep thy words.

verses.text_plain: I intreated thy favour with my whole heart: be merciful unto me according to thy word.
verses.verse_html:
58I intreated thy favour with my whole heart: be merciful unto me according to thy word. ▼
▼ favour: Heb. face

tokens.text: unto me according to thy word

footnotes.body_html: ▼ favour: Heb. face

verses.text_plain: I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html: 59I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.

verses.text_plain: I made haste, and delayed not to keep thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 60I made haste, and delayed not to keep thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: The bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten thy law.
verses.verse_html:
61The bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten thy law. ▼
▼ bands: or, companies

footnotes.body_html: ▼ bands: or, companies

verses.text_plain: At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.
verses.verse_html: 62At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.

tokens.text: unto thee because of thy righteous

verses.text_plain: I am a companion of all them that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 63I am a companion of all them that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.

tokens.text: thee, and of them that keep

verses.text_plain: The earth, O Lord, is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 64The earth, O Lord, is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O Lord, according unto thy word.
verses.verse_html: 65Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O Lord, according unto thy word.

verses.text_plain: Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 66Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: Before I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept thy word.
verses.verse_html: 67Before I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept thy word.

verses.text_plain: Thou art good, and doest good; teach me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 68Thou art good, and doest good; teach me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: The proud have forged a lie against me: but I will keep thy precepts with my whole heart.
verses.verse_html: 69The proud have forged a lie against me: but I will keep thy precepts with my whole heart.

verses.text_plain: Their heart is as fat as grease; but I delight in thy law.
verses.verse_html: 70Their heart is as fat as grease; but I delight in thy law.

verses.text_plain: It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 71It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.

tokens.text: for me that I have been afflicted

verses.text_plain: The law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.
verses.verse_html: 72The law of thy mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.

verses.text_plain: Thy hands have made me and fashioned me: give me understanding, that I may learn thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 73Thy hands have made me and fashioned me: give me understanding, that I may learn thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: They that fear thee will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in thy word.
verses.verse_html: 74They that fear thee will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in thy word.

verses.text_plain: I know, O Lord, that thy judgments are right, and that thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me.
verses.verse_html:
75I know, O Lord, that thy judgments are right, and that thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me. ▼
▼ right: Heb. righteousness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ right: Heb. righteousness

verses.text_plain: Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant.
verses.verse_html:
76Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant. ▼
▼ for…: Heb. to comfort me

tokens.text: Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ for…: Heb. to comfort me

verses.text_plain: Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law is my delight.
verses.verse_html: 77Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law is my delight.

tokens.text: unto me, that I may live

verses.text_plain: Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 78Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: Let those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html: 79Let those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.

tokens.text: unto me, and those that have known

verses.text_plain: Let my heart be sound in thy statutes; that I be not ashamed.
verses.verse_html: 80Let my heart be sound in thy statutes; that I be not ashamed.

verses.text_plain: My soul fainteth for thy salvation: but I hope in thy word.
verses.verse_html: 81My soul fainteth for thy salvation: but I hope in thy word.

verses.text_plain: Mine eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me?
verses.verse_html: 82Mine eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me?

verses.text_plain: For I am become like a bottle in the smoke; yet do I not forget thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 83For I am become like a bottle in the smoke; yet do I not forget thy statutes.

tokens.text: For I am become like a bottle

verses.text_plain: How many are the days of thy servant? when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me?
verses.verse_html: 84How many are the days of thy servant? when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me?

verses.text_plain: The proud have digged pits for me, which are not after thy law.
verses.verse_html: 85The proud have digged pits for me, which are not after thy law.

verses.text_plain: All thy commandments are faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help thou me.
verses.verse_html:
86All thy commandments are faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help thou me. ▼
▼ faithful: Heb. faithfulness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ faithful: Heb. faithfulness

verses.text_plain: They had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 87They had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: Quicken me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.
verses.verse_html: 88Quicken me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.

verses.text_plain: For ever, O Lord, thy word is settled in heaven.
verses.verse_html: 89For ever, O Lord, thy word is settled in heaven.

verses.text_plain: Thy faithfulness is unto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.
verses.verse_html:
90Thy faithfulness is unto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth. ▼

 , ▼

footnotes.body_html: ▼ unto…: Heb. to generation and generation
▼ abideth: Heb. standeth

verses.text_plain: They continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all are thy servants.
verses.verse_html: 91They continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all are thy servants.

verses.text_plain: Unless thy law had been my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.
verses.verse_html: 92Unless thy law had been my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.

verses.text_plain: I will never forget thy precepts: for with them thou hast quickened me.
verses.verse_html: 93I will never forget thy precepts: for with them thou hast quickened me.

tokens.text: for with them thou hast quickened

verses.text_plain: I am thine, save me; for I have sought thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 94I am thine, save me; for I have sought thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: The wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html: 95The wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider thy testimonies.

verses.text_plain: I have seen an end of all perfection: but thy commandment is exceeding broad.
verses.verse_html: 96I have seen an end of all perfection: but thy commandment is exceeding broad.

verses.text_plain: O how love I thy law! it is my meditation all the day.
verses.verse_html: 97O how love I thy law! it is my meditation all the day.

verses.text_plain: Thou through thy commandments hast made me wiser than mine enemies: for they are ever with me.
verses.verse_html:
98Thou through thy commandments hast made me wiser than mine enemies: for they are ever with me. ▼
▼ they…: Heb. it is ever with me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they…: Heb. it is ever with me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they…: Heb. it is ever with me

verses.text_plain: I have more understanding than all my teachers: for thy testimonies are my meditation.
verses.verse_html: 99I have more understanding than all my teachers: for thy testimonies are my meditation.

verses.text_plain: I understand more than the ancients, because I keep thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 100I understand more than the ancients, because I keep thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.
verses.verse_html: 101I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.

verses.text_plain: I have not departed from thy judgments: for thou hast taught me.
verses.verse_html: 102I have not departed from thy judgments: for thou hast taught me.

verses.text_plain: How sweet are thy words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
verses.verse_html:
103How sweet are thy words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth! ▼
▼ taste: Heb. palate

footnotes.body_html: ▼ taste: Heb. palate

verses.text_plain: Through thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.
verses.verse_html: 104Through thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.

verses.text_plain: Thy word is a lamp unto my feet, and a light unto my path.
verses.verse_html:
105Thy word is a lamp unto my feet, and a light unto my path. ▼
▼ lamp: or, candle

footnotes.body_html: ▼ lamp: or, candle

verses.text_plain: I have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.
verses.verse_html: 106I have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.

verses.text_plain: I am afflicted very much: quicken me, O Lord, according unto thy word.
verses.verse_html: 107I am afflicted very much: quicken me, O Lord, according unto thy word.

verses.text_plain: Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O Lord, and teach me thy judgments.
verses.verse_html: 108Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O Lord, and teach me thy judgments.

tokens.text: I beseech thee, the freewill offerings

verses.text_plain: My soul is continually in my hand: yet do I not forget thy law.
verses.verse_html: 109My soul is continually in my hand: yet do I not forget thy law.

verses.text_plain: The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 110The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage for ever: for they are the rejoicing of my heart.
verses.verse_html: 111Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage for ever: for they are the rejoicing of my heart.

tokens.text: have I taken as an heritage

verses.text_plain: I have inclined mine heart to perform thy statutes alway, even unto the end.
verses.verse_html:
112I have inclined mine heart to perform thy statutes alway, even unto the end. ▼
▼ to perform: Heb. to do

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to perform: Heb. to do

verses.text_plain: I hate vain thoughts: but thy law do I love.
verses.verse_html: 113I hate vain thoughts: but thy law do I love.

verses.text_plain: Thou art my hiding place and my shield: I hope in thy word.
verses.verse_html: 114Thou art my hiding place and my shield: I hope in thy word.

verses.text_plain: Depart from me, ye evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.
verses.verse_html: 115Depart from me, ye evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.

verses.verse_html: 116Uphold me according unto thy word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.

tokens.text: and let me not be ashamed

verses.verse_html: 117Hold thou me up, and I shall be safe: and I will have respect unto thy statutes continually.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes: for their deceit is falsehood.
verses.verse_html: 118Thou hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes: for their deceit is falsehood.

119Thou puttest away all the wicked of the earth like dross: therefore I love thy testimonies. ▼

verses.verse_html: 120My flesh trembleth for fear of thee; and I am afraid of thy judgments.

tokens.text: of thee; and I am afraid

verses.verse_html: 121I have done judgment and justice: leave me not to mine oppressors.

verses.verse_html: 122Be surety for thy servant for good: let not the proud oppress me.

verses.verse_html: 123Mine eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.

verses.verse_html: 124Deal with thy servant according unto thy mercy, and teach me thy statutes.

verses.verse_html: 125I am thy servant; give me understanding, that I may know thy testimonies.

verses.verse_html: 126It is time for thee, Lord, to work: for they have made void thy law.

verses.text_plain: Therefore I love thy commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.
verses.verse_html: 127Therefore I love thy commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.

verses.text_plain: Therefore I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right; and I hate every false way.
verses.verse_html: 128Therefore I esteem all thy precepts concerning all things to be right; and I hate every false way.

verses.text_plain: Thy testimonies are wonderful: therefore doth my soul keep them.
verses.verse_html: 129Thy testimonies are wonderful: therefore doth my soul keep them.

verses.text_plain: The entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple.
verses.verse_html: 130The entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple.

verses.text_plain: I opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 131I opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: Look thou upon me, and be merciful unto me, as thou usest to do unto those that love thy name.
verses.verse_html:
132Look thou upon me, and be merciful unto me, as thou usest to do unto those that love thy name. ▼
▼ as thou…: Heb. according to the custom toward those, etc

tokens.text: thou upon me, and be merciful
to do unto those that love

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as thou…: Heb. according to the custom toward those, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as thou…: Heb. according to the custom toward those, etc

verses.text_plain: Order my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.
verses.verse_html: 133Order my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.

verses.text_plain: Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 134Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: Make thy face to shine upon thy servant; and teach me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 135Make thy face to shine upon thy servant; and teach me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.
verses.verse_html: 136Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.

verses.text_plain: Righteous art thou, O Lord, and upright are thy judgments.
verses.verse_html: 137Righteous art thou, O Lord, and upright are thy judgments.

verses.text_plain: Thy testimonies that thou hast commanded are righteous and very faithful.
verses.verse_html:
138Thy testimonies that thou hast commanded are righteous and very faithful. ▼
▼ righteous: Heb. righteousness
 , ▼
▼ faithful: Heb. faithfulness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ righteous: Heb. righteousness
▼ faithful: Heb. faithfulness

verses.text_plain: My zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words.
verses.verse_html:
139My zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words. ▼
▼ consumed…: Heb. cut me off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ consumed…: Heb. cut me off

verses.text_plain: Thy word is very pure: therefore thy servant loveth it.
verses.verse_html:
140Thy word is very pure: therefore thy servant loveth it. ▼
▼ pure: Heb. tried, or, refined

footnotes.body_html: ▼ pure: Heb. tried, or, refined

verses.text_plain: I am small and despised: yet do not I forget thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 141I am small and despised: yet do not I forget thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and thy law is the truth.
verses.verse_html: 142Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and thy law is the truth.

verses.text_plain: Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me: yet thy commandments are my delights.
verses.verse_html:
143Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me: yet thy commandments are my delights. ▼
▼ taken…: Heb. found me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ taken…: Heb. found me

verses.text_plain: The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.
verses.verse_html: 144The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.

verses.text_plain: I cried with my whole heart; hear me, O Lord: I will keep thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 145I cried with my whole heart; hear me, O Lord: I will keep thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: I cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html:
146I cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies. ▼
▼ and I…: or, that I may keep

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and I…: or, that I may keep
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and I…: or, that I may keep

verses.text_plain: I prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in thy word.
verses.verse_html: 147I prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in thy word.

verses.text_plain: Mine eyes prevent the night watches, that I might meditate in thy word.
verses.verse_html: 148Mine eyes prevent the night watches, that I might meditate in thy word.

verses.text_plain: Hear my voice according unto thy lovingkindness: O Lord, quicken me according to thy judgment.
verses.verse_html: 149Hear my voice according unto thy lovingkindness: O Lord, quicken me according to thy judgment.

verses.text_plain: They draw nigh that follow after mischief: they are far from thy law.
verses.verse_html: 150They draw nigh that follow after mischief: they are far from thy law.

verses.text_plain: Thou art near, O Lord; and all thy commandments are truth.
verses.verse_html: 151Thou art near, O Lord; and all thy commandments are truth.

verses.text_plain: Concerning thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them for ever.
verses.verse_html: 152Concerning thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them for ever.

verses.text_plain: Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.
verses.verse_html: 153Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.

tokens.text: me: for I do not forget

verses.text_plain: Plead my cause, and deliver me: quicken me according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 154Plead my cause, and deliver me: quicken me according to thy word.

verses.text_plain: Salvation is far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 155Salvation is far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: Great are thy tender mercies, O Lord: quicken me according to thy judgments.
verses.verse_html:
156Great are thy tender mercies, O Lord: quicken me according to thy judgments. ▼
▼ Great: or, Many

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Great: or, Many

verses.text_plain: Many are my persecutors and mine enemies; yet do I not decline from thy testimonies.
verses.verse_html: 157Many are my persecutors and mine enemies; yet do I not decline from thy testimonies.

verses.text_plain: I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not thy word.
verses.verse_html: 158I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not thy word.

verses.text_plain: Consider how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O Lord, according to thy lovingkindness.
verses.verse_html: 159Consider how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O Lord, according to thy lovingkindness.

verses.text_plain: Thy word is true from the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html:
160Thy word is true from the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth for ever. ▼
▼ Thy word…: Heb. The beginning of thy word is true

tokens.text: and every one of thy righteous

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Thy word…: Heb. The beginning of thy word is true
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Thy word…: Heb. The beginning of thy word is true

verses.text_plain: Princes have persecuted me without a cause: but my heart standeth in awe of thy word.
verses.verse_html: 161Princes have persecuted me without a cause: but my heart standeth in awe of thy word.

verses.text_plain: I rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.
verses.verse_html: 162I rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.

verses.text_plain: I hate and abhor lying: but thy law do I love.
verses.verse_html: 163I hate and abhor lying: but thy law do I love.

verses.text_plain: Seven times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.
verses.verse_html: 164Seven times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.

verses.text_plain: Great peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them.
verses.verse_html:
165Great peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them. ▼
▼ nothing…: Heb. they shall have no stumblingblock

footnotes.body_text: ▼ nothing…: Heb. they shall have no stumblingblock
footnotes.body_html: ▼ nothing…: Heb. they shall have no stumblingblock

verses.text_plain: Lord, I have hoped for thy salvation, and done thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 166Lord, I have hoped for thy salvation, and done thy commandments.

verses.text_plain: My soul hath kept thy testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.
verses.verse_html: 167My soul hath kept thy testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.

verses.text_plain: I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways are before thee.
verses.verse_html: 168I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways are before thee.

verses.text_plain: Let my cry come near before thee, O Lord: give me understanding according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 169Let my cry come near before thee, O Lord: give me understanding according to thy word.

verses.text_plain: Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.
verses.verse_html: 170Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.

verses.text_plain: My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.
verses.verse_html: 171My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.

verses.text_plain: My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments are righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 172My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments are righteousness.

verses.text_plain: Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.
verses.verse_html: 173Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.

verses.text_plain: I have longed for thy salvation, O Lord; and thy law is my delight.
verses.verse_html: 174I have longed for thy salvation, O Lord; and thy law is my delight.

verses.text_plain: Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.
verses.verse_html: 175Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.

verses.text_plain: I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.
verses.verse_html: 176I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.
